news.title: Cidco seeks to convert leasehold land into freehold: Chairman
news.para: Under the existing Cidco's leasehold policy, land acquired for city development across Maharashtra is allotted to lessees for a period of 60 years, with Cidco retaining ownership rights.

news.title: Ramco Cements increases grinding capacity by nearly one MTPA
news.para: In addition, at its Valapady Grinding Unit, in Salem District, Tamil Nadu, it has carried out debottlenecking of cement grinding capacity leading to increase of capacity from 1.6 MTPA to 2 MTPA.

news.title: Finance minister reviews capex plan of housing and urban affairs ministry
news.para: For the financial year 2024-25, a budgetary allocation of Rs 28,628 crore has been earmarked for capital expenditure. During the meeting, the Finance Minister emphasized the need for timely and efficient utilisation of these funds, the ministry said.

news.title: Haryana government revokes its decision to pause implementation of S+4 floor policy
news.para: The decision came after the department retracted an earlier statement submitted to the Punjab and Haryana high court, pausing the implementation of the policy which had faced strong opposition from Gurgaon Citizens Council (GCC). The council had filed a petition in the high court, seeking to overturn the new rules.

news.title: Rare Enterprises' CEO buys apartment for Rs 123 crore in Mumbai’s Worli
news.para: Sheth was considered the late billionaire investor Jhunjhunwala's right hand man for almost two decades and is also a cofounder of multi-line and multi-asset financial services platform Trust Group.

news.title: ED seizes Rs 42 crore assets from Noida authority's ex-CEO, builders in PMLA case
news.para: The ED conducted raids at 18 locations in Delhi, Noida and Meerut in UP as well as Chandigarh and Goa on Sept 18-19 as part of an investigation into alleged fraud by Hacienda Projects Private Limited (HPPL), its promoters and directors and related entities.

news.title: EQT acquires 100% stake in Indostar Home Finance for Rs 1,750 crore
news.para: Founded in 2017, Indostar Home Finance provides affordable mortgages to retail customers in tier 2 to tier 4 cities in India and has supported over 39,000 low-income homeowners and small businesses.

news.title: Noida residents struggles with construction waste as traffic increases
news.para: Its lone management facility in Sector 80 processes — turns debris into usable sand and gravel that is recognised as a good substitute for natural sand in concrete mix — about 400 to 500 tonnes brought to it.

news.title: Home prices in Germany fall 2.6% in Q2 2024
news.para: The annual declines have slowed over recent quarters, and prices rose 1.3% in the second quarter from the first three months of the year, the first quarter-on-quarter increase since 2022.

news.title: Mumbai: Illegal reclamation destroys mangroves, saltwater lake in Wadala
news.para: "Due to its proximity to the Freeway, the realty land value of this Wadala site has gone up, which is why the water body area, which is equivalent to 1.5 times a football field (around 1.76 acres), is being reclaimed through debris dumping.

news.title: US: Builders' stocks surge as Federal Reserve's rate-cut expected
news.para: The U.S. central bank on Wednesday kicked off an anticipated series of interest rate cuts with a larger-than-usual half-percentage-point reduction that is expected to further reduce mortgage rates in the coming months and help reduce incentives that builders need to offer to attract buyers.

news.title: Home construction approvals in UK hit lowest in June
news.para: Data from the Home Builders Federation, the industry's main trade body, showed around 230,000 units received planning permission in the 12 months to June, the least for any 12-month period since 2014.

news.title: NCLAT stays order to restart Rajesh Business' bankruptcy process
news.para: The Rs 492 crore resolution plan by a Rare ARC-Check-Inn Hotels Pvt Ltd consortium had envisaged about 79% recovery on lender dues of more than Rs 621 crore. But more than a year after the committee of creditors (CoC) had approved the plan, a Mumbai bench of the NCLT ordered a fresh process citing procedural issues that ICICI Bank had challenged.

news.title: Vietnam's Truong My Lan faces second trial for $12.5 billion financial fraud
news.para: Her arrest and conviction was one of the highest profile cases in an anti-corruption drive that has intensified since 2022. The so-called blazing furnace campaign has also singed the highest echelons of Vietnamese politics and led to the resignation of a former president who was implicated in it.

news.title: BBMP to geotag properties for issuing digital e-khatas in Bengaluru
news.para: As part of this process, BBMP staff will soon visit properties across the city to capture their GPS coordinates. This data will serve as a unique identity marker for each property, which is crucial for online delivery of e-khata services.

news.title: Maharashtra government allocates Rs 188.3 crore funds to MMRCL, Rs 165 crore to Pune Metro
news.para: In a Govt Resolution issued on Thursday, the state urban development dept said a decision has been made to allocate funds to Mumbai Metro Rail Corporation Limited and Maharashtra Metro Rail Corporation (MahaMetro) as per the details shown in the budget for the year 2024-25 under the one percent additional tax surcharge.

news.title: Residents of MUDA approved layouts in Mysuru outskirts struggle for amenities
news.para: A dispute between Muda and the newly-formed Hootagalli City Municipal Council (CMC) has left residents, who are paying taxes to Muda, without essential services, residents complained. Neither Muda nor the Hootagalli CMC have stepped in to resolve the issue, localities alleged.

news.title: Shine City Group's vice president arrested in investment scam
news.para: ADCP North Jitendra Kumar Dubey said that there was a reward of 50,000 on the accused Manish Jaiswal, and the police had been searching for him for about a year. He said cases of fraud had been registered against Manish in Lucknow and Prayagraj.

news.title: Developers in NCR allowed non-polluting work during construction ban: CAQM
news.para: This year, the authority has listed activities which will be banned, instead of imposing a blanket ban on construction activities if the air quality turns "severe" (stage III), said industry executives, This will allow developers to continue with some interior work, they said.
